physical_appearance: This is a photograph of the Shwedagon Pagoda in Rangoon, Burma. The photograph shows a pavilion with a tiered decorated roof. The base of the pavilion is supported by columns around its circumference. There are several people at the entrance of the pagoda. The pavilion is surrounded by trees on either side. The title is written at the bottom, below the photograph.
title_text: Photograph album of views and portraits in the Punjab, Cashmere, Ceylon, Burma, Penang, Singapore, and Java Upper entrance of Shwedagon Pagoda, Rangoon
